	Now, you should leave the basic page template alone and make copies of it for each page you want in the help book. For each page:\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Change the <title> to the title of the page.\
{\listtext	2.	}Provide keywords in the meta "keywords" tag. These are used by the Help Viewer's search function, so make them useful.\
{\listtext	3.	}Provide an abstract of the page in the meta "description" tag.\
{\listtext	4.	}Change "SOMECATEGORY" in the <a> anchor to a reasonable category or delete the anchor if you don't want the page to belong to a category. You can make links to an auto-generated list of all pages in a given category using the template at the bottom of this page.\
{\listtext	5.	}Change the header in the "pagetitle" div to match what you put in <title>.\
{\listtext	6.	}Change the lipsum text to the documentation for the page. Try to make it as short as possible.\
{\listtext	7.	}If possible, insert a screenshot. These spice up the pages and help users get an idea of what's going on. If you can't put in a screenshot, make sure to delete the <img> tag. Remember to shrink the screenshot if it's bigger than 350px wide or so.\
{\listtext	8.	}Provide useful "See also" links at the bottom of the page (see the HTML for example links).\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
