\f0\b\fs28 Using Your Help Book\
\

\f1\b0\fs24 	Once you've finished your lovely help book, you still need to do a few things before your application will know it exists.\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Put these files in a "YOURAPP Help" folder inside English.lproj (or whatever language).\
{\listtext	2.	}Drag the "YOURAPP Help" folder into the resources folder in your Xcode project. Make 
\f2\i sure
\f1\i0  to choose the "make folder references option".\
{\listtext	3.	}Add keys for CFBundleHelpBookFolder and CFBundleHelpBookName to Info.plist and set them both to "YOURAPP Help".\
{\listtext	4.	}Drop the "YOURAPP Help" folder into Help Indexer.\
{\listtext	5.	}Compile and run!\
